President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. The nominations and appointments include Andrew H. Giuliani, Nicholas F. Luna, and Mitch Webber as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Julie T. Radford is nominated to be a member of the Community Development Advisory Board, while Professor Adam Candeub and James O’Neill are appointed as members of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. Kristan King Nevins is also appointed as a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. Other appointments include Gibson Worsham as a member of the National Capital Planning Commission, Anna Cristina “Rickie” Niceta as a member of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation, and Suzanna Sexton, Jeannie Leauma, and Teri Geston as members of the President’s Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities. Lastly, Munr Kazmir and David D’Arcangelo are appointed as members of the National Council on Disability.